commit.message: Check certificate validity before accepting local-PKI root.
Bump version numbers to 0.09
Fix for CSS overlay.

Fix notary proxy logic.

The move to physical notaries broke the proxy logic for
individual notary connections.  This fixes proxying support
for multi-connect to destinations with proxies defined, although
it still uses a roughly scoped proxy definition.
Advanced configuration options for whitelisting rfc1918 address space and private PKIs.
Support for notary locale, smart bouncing, and quorum thresholds.
Exempt RFC1918 addresses from Convergence.
Support for 'local PKI' exemptions.
Remove client certificate support.
Bump version to 0.08
Support for Gecko 8 change to ChromeWorker factory API.
Bundle script requires at least one physical host.
Support for client certificates.
Disable Convergence if user does not unlock PSM.
Remove full encoded certificate details from debug log.
Reload page after confirming Convergence exception.
Bumped client version to 0.07
Bump server version to 0.4
Added correct non-blocking write functionality.
NSPR apparently can't flip Windows FDs back to blocking once they've been non-blocking, so we just leave them non-blocking and deal.
Temporary remove the crypto project from notary defaults.
Add The Crypto Project and Qualys as defaults.
Fixed bugs in .notary bundle loading.
Fix certificate formatting in bundle.
Add thoughtcrime.notary bundle auto-update location to defaults.
Added bundle location to bundle creation tool.
Add notary bundle auto-update support.
Updated bundle creation script for new notary format.
Duplicate notary detection.
Notary bundle version backwards compatibility.
